natural language q: List the contestant numbers and names, ordered by contestant name descending.
sql: SELECT contestant_number ,  contestant_name FROM contestants ORDER BY contestant_name DESC
sql_result: (2, 'Tabatha Gehling'), (8, 'Nita Coster'), (11, 'Loraine NygrenTania Mattioli'), (9, 'Kurt Walser'), (3, 'Kelly Clauss'), (6, 'Jessie Eichman'), (4, 'Jessie Alloway'), (10, 'Ericka Dieter'), (1, 'Edwina Burnam'), (7, 'Allie Rogalski'), (5, 'Alana Bregman')
sparql: select ?t1_contestant_number ?t1_contestant_name where { ?t1 a dbo:contestants . ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_number ?t1_contestant_number . ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_name ?t1_contestant_name . ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_name ?t1_contestant_name .        }  order by desc (?t1_contestant_name)
sparql_result: (2, 'Tabatha Gehling'), (8, 'Nita Coster'), (11, 'Loraine NygrenTania Mattioli'), (9, 'Kurt Walser'), (3, 'Kelly Clauss'), (6, 'Jessie Eichman'), (4, 'Jessie Alloway'), (10, 'Ericka Dieter'), (1, 'Edwina Burnam'), (7, 'Allie Rogalski'), (5, 'Alana Bregman')

natural language q: List the vote ids, phone numbers and states of all votes.
sql: SELECT vote_id ,  phone_number , state FROM votes as T1 join area_code_state as T2 on T1.area_code = T2.area_code
sparql: select ?t1_vote_id ?t1_phone_number ?t2_state where { ?t1 a dbo:votes . ?t2 a dbo:area_code_state . ?t1 dbo:votes\#ref-area_code ?t2 .  ?t1 dbo:votes\#vote_id ?t1_vote_id . ?t1 dbo:votes\#phone_number ?t1_phone_number . ?t2 dbo:area_code_state\#state ?t2_state .        }

natural language q: What are the maximum and minimum values of area codes?
sparql: select (max( ?t1_area_code) as ?aggregation_t1_area_code_374 ) (min( ?t1_area_code) as ?aggregation_t1_area_code_87 ) where { ?t1 a dbo:area_code_state . ?t1 dbo:area_code_state\#area_code ?t1_area_code . ?t1 dbo:area_code_state\#area_code ?t1_area_code .        }

natural language q: What is last date created of votes from the state 'CA'?
sql: SELECT max(created) FROM votes as T1 join area_code_state as T2 on T1.area_code = T2.area_code WHERE state  =  'CA'
sparql: select (max( ?t1_created) as ?aggregation_t1_created_177 ) where { ?t1 a dbo:votes . ?t2 a dbo:area_code_state . ?t1 dbo:votes\#ref-area_code ?t2 .  ?t1 dbo:votes\#created ?t1_created . ?t2 dbo:area_code_state\#state ?t2_state . FILTER(?t2_state = 'CA') .        }

natural language q: What are the distinct states and create time of all votes?
sql: SELECT DISTINCT state , created FROM votes as T1 join area_code_state as T2 on T1.area_code = T2.area_code
sparql: select distinct ?t1_state ?t2_created where { ?t1 a dbo:area_code_state . ?t2 a dbo:votes . ?t2 dbo:votes\#ref-area_code ?t1 .  ?t1 dbo:area_code_state\#state ?t1_state . ?t2 dbo:votes\#created ?t2_created .        }

natural language q: What are the contestant numbers and names of the contestants who had at least two votes?
sql: SELECT T1.contestant_number , T1.contestant_name FROM contestants AS T1 JOIN votes AS T2 ON T1.contestant_number  =  T2.contestant_number GROUP BY T1.contestant_number HAVING count(*)  >=  2
sparql: select ?t1_contestant_number ?t1_contestant_name where { ?t1 a dbo:contestants . ?t2 a dbo:votes . ?t2 dbo:votes\#ref-contestant_number ?t1 .  ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_number ?t1_contestant_number . ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_name ?t1_contestant_name . ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_number ?t1_contestant_number .        } group by ?t1_contestant_number ?t1_contestant_name   having(count( *)  >= 2)

natural language q: Of all the contestants who got voted, what is the contestant number and name of the contestant who got least votes?
sql: SELECT T1.contestant_number , T1.contestant_name FROM contestants AS T1 JOIN votes AS T2 ON T1.contestant_number  =  T2.contestant_number GROUP BY T1.contestant_number ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1
sparql: select ?t1_contestant_number ?t1_contestant_name where { ?t1 a dbo:contestants . ?t2 a dbo:votes . ?t2 dbo:votes\#ref-contestant_number ?t1 .  ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_number ?t1_contestant_number . ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_name ?t1_contestant_name . ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_number ?t1_contestant_number .        } group by ?t1_contestant_number ?t1_contestant_name  order by asc (count(*)) limit 1

natural language q: What are the number of votes from state 'NY' or 'CA'?
sql: SELECT count(*) FROM votes as T1 join area_code_state as T2 on T1.area_code = T2.area_code WHERE state  =  'NY' OR state  =  'CA'
sparql: select (count( *) as ?aggregation_all) where { ?t1 a dbo:votes . ?t2 a dbo:area_code_state . ?t1 dbo:votes\#ref-area_code ?t2 .  ?t2 dbo:area_code_state\#state ?t2_state . ?t2 dbo:area_code_state\#state ?t2_state . FILTER(?t2_state = 'NY' || ?t2_state = 'CA') .        }

natural language q: How many contestants did not get voted?
sql: SELECT count(*) FROM contestants WHERE contestant_number NOT IN ( SELECT contestant_number FROM votes )
sparql: select (count( *) as ?aggregation_all) where { ?t1 a dbo:contestants . ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_number ?t1_contestant_number .     Filter not exists {{select ?t22_contestant_number where { ?t22 a dbo:votes . ?t22 dbo:votes\#contestant_number ?t22_contestant_number .        }    } FILTER (?t1_contestant_number in (?t22_contestant_number))}  }

natural language q: What is the area code in which the most voters voted?
sql: SELECT T1.area_code FROM area_code_state AS T1 JOIN votes AS T2 ON T1.area_code  =  T2.area_code GROUP BY T1.area_code ORDER BY count(*)
sparql: select ?t1_area_code where { ?t1 a dbo:area_code_state . ?t2 a dbo:votes . ?t2 dbo:votes\#ref-area_code ?t1 .  ?t1 dbo:area_code_state\#area_code ?t1_area_code . ?t1 dbo:area_code_state\#state ?t1_state .        } group by ?t1_area_code  order by desc (count(*)) limit 1

natural language q: What are the create dates, states, and phone numbers of the votes that were for the contestant named 'Tabatha Gehling'?
sql: SELECT T2.created , T2.phone_number,  T3.state FROM contestants AS T1 JOIN votes AS T2 ON T1.contestant_number  =  T2.contestant_number join area_code_state as T3 on T3.area_code = T2.area_code WHERE T1.contestant_name  =  'Tabatha Gehling'
sparql: select ?t1_created ?t2_state ?t1_phone_number where { ?t1 a dbo:votes . ?t2 a dbo:area_code_state . ?t1 dbo:votes\#ref-area_code ?t2 .  ?t1 dbo:votes\#created ?t1_created . ?t2 dbo:area_code_state\#state ?t2_state . ?t1 dbo:votes\#phone_number ?t1_phone_number . ?t3 dbo:contestants\#contestant_name ?t3_contestant_name . ?t3 a dbo:contestants . ?t1 dbo:votes\#ref-contestant_number ?t3 .  ?t1 dbo:votes\#created ?t1_created . ?t2 dbo:area_code_state\#state ?t2_state . ?t1 dbo:votes\#phone_number ?t1_phone_number . ?t3 dbo:contestants\#contestant_name ?t3_contestant_name . FILTER(?t3_contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling') .        }

FILTER(?t2_contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling') . FILTER(?t5_contestant_name = 'Kelly Clauss') .     }      }

natural language q: Return the names the contestants whose names contain the substring 'Al'.
sql: SELECT contestant_name FROM contestants WHERE contestant_name LIKE '%Al%'
sparql: select ?t1_contestant_name where { ?t1 a dbo:contestants . ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_name ?t1_contestant_name . ?t1 dbo:contestants\#contestant_name ?t1_contestant_name . FILTER(contains (?t1_contestant_name, 'Al')) .        }
